Class MockCollectionDAO

java.lang.Object
com.example.cab302assessment10b0101.model.MockCollectionDAO
All Implemented Interfaces:
CollectionDAOInterface
public class MockCollectionDAO extends Object implements CollectionDAOInterface
The MockCollectionDAO class is a mock implementation of the CollectionDAOInterface. It is used to simulate the behavior of the actual CollectionDAO in unit tests. This class stores Collection objects in-memory using a List and provides methods to simulate database operations such as insert, retrieve all collections, and retrieve collections by user.
